        "timestamp": "2019-12-12 20:30:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(5 comments)\n\nLooks okay except for removing lines that override setting of sli core version to ${project.version}.  This makes sense during development to make sure that, if we change parent poms to use released version (for CCSDK consumers), we don't break our internal builds.  At some point, we'll want to change that to a specific version (e.g. 0.7.0) for the same reason, but right now all CCSDK repos should use same snapshot version.",
        "patchset_number": 1
